{{see|volva|vọlva}}

==English==

===Etymology===
From the Old Norse [[vọlva]] \ [[#Old Norse|völva]].

===Noun===
'''völva'''
# in Old Norse society, a female [[practitioner]] of magic divination and prophecy
# (''by extension'') any prophetess, sooth-sayer, or witch

